{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/retinal-detachment/diagnosis/assessment/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"9769ec04-f525-59c3-b435-b9d3102c8181","slug":"assessment","fullItemName":"Assessment","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field db2fef0b-d3d3-458a-9413-aab60116bf47 --><h2>How should I assess a person with suspected retinal detachment?</h2><!-- end field db2fef0b-d3d3-458a-9413-aab60116bf47 -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 5ed2d4cf-c711-435a-abf7-aab60116bf0d --><!-- begin field 966d59fb-1a73-45f3-9d1c-aab60116bf47 --><p><strong>If a person has <a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/retinal-detachment/diagnosis/diagnosis/\">suspected</a> retinal detachment:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Ask about:</strong><ul><li>The characteristics, duration, and laterality of any flashes or floaters — flashes may be more noticeable in dim light.</li><li>The size, shape, and distribution of any floaters — floaters may be more noticeable against a bright uniform background, such as a computer screen or white paper.</li><li>The onset, nature, and duration of any change in vision.</li><li>Any personal or family history of retinal break or retinal detachment.</li><li>Any other <a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/retinal-detachment/background-information/risk-factors/\">risk factors</a> for retinal detachment, including co-morbidities and history of eye trauma.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Examine for:</strong><ul><li>Reduced visual acuity using a Snellen chart — vision may be reduced to finger counting or hand movements if the macula is detached.</li><li>Peripheral visual field loss by performing confrontational fields testing.</li><li>A relative afferent pupillary defect if there is extensive detachment — using the swinging flashlight test, the pupil dilates rather than constricts or stays the same size when light is shone on it, suggesting optic nerve disease.</li><li>Fundoscopic findings of an asymmetric red reflex, vitreous opacities, or detached retinal folds which appear pale, opaque, and wrinkled, in larger detachments. Note that no fundoscopic abnormality may be seen if the detachment is small.</li><li>A white pupillary reflex (leukocoria) or squint (strabismus) in infants, which are typical presenting signs of retinal detachment in this age group.</li></ul></li></ul><!-- end field 966d59fb-1a73-45f3-9d1c-aab60116bf47 --><!-- end item 5ed2d4cf-c711-435a-abf7-aab60116bf0d -->","topic":{"id":"9be2cb0d-8648-5694-a09c-292ca1ced19e","topicId":"e3f75bdf-a207-4239-9931-367d38a9b7d6","topicName":"Retinal detachment","slug":"retinal-detachment","lastRevised":"Last revised in August 2019","chapters":[{"id":"842ff08c-c002-50cd-bab2-348ba3e67be0","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"98f29b98-1286-5c16-a606-4cd90cc70465","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"873d5520-2d22-5b9d-bd04-6d9112dc82ee","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"3b54abb3-d415-51e3-996b-1d6e3bcc3d3b","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"0aa87cea-a601-54db-9dcb-ec3117e7098a","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"dbe4b4fd-c326-5686-bd9a-71905fc13c76","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"9f38c5e9-5edd-56fa-a740-0d19004a69af","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"5960233a-64c2-5a35-95ea-6a44ae788808","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"e506d9ce-54a0-57f2-b4d1-49bb28e3d283","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria"},{"id":"0ce8a869-7cf6-588c-b609-d5a90fa6adf0","slug":"qof-indicators","fullItemName":"QOF indicators"},{"id":"a1808dfe-2608-5274-a314-61a4054cb431","slug":"qipp-options-for-local-implementation","fullItemName":"QIPP - Options for local implementation"},{"id":"6148c790-0603-5594-9e2f-9d1a8bdaab45","slug":"nice-quality-standards","fullItemName":"NICE quality standards"}]},{"id":"17128c85-3baa-5f71-a71e-69028c5e8e6a","fullItemName":"Background information","slug":"background-information","subChapters":[{"id":"4d268a45-69b2-5f94-9f83-4e3bde2a12b8","slug":"definition","fullItemName":"Definition"},{"id":"7d44ea0b-28de-57c5-9ffa-bc6337cf6d42","slug":"prevalence","fullItemName":"Prevalence"},{"id":"85ba124b-cb79-55bf-970f-0ad15fc8f02d","slug":"risk-factors","fullItemName":"Risk factors"},{"id":"297f94a6-ea6d-5e98-8a9b-643eab61b543","slug":"prognosis","fullItemName":"Prognosis"},{"id":"b6f559a3-be4e-53c3-b812-d240ecc27130","slug":"complications","fullItemName":"Complications"}]},{"id":"043a146b-8512-55b9-9f09-5d5cfe0e6149","fullItemName":"Diagnosis","slug":"diagnosis","subChapters":[{"id":"8f1c2235-30d5-59ca-b646-048edf6147eb","slug":"diagnosis","fullItemName":"Diagnosis"},{"id":"9769ec04-f525-59c3-b435-b9d3102c8181","slug":"assessment","fullItemName":"Assessment"},{"id":"06def8c4-72e1-5803-9856-4a5dc3251143","slug":"differential-diagnosis","fullItemName":"Differential diagnosis"}]},{"id":"f6051a87-5d54-56c8-a89a-c0b31d5792cf","fullItemName":"Management","slug":"management","subChapters":[{"id":"ae8728b5-6ae9-581c-8fae-9459f97d2aa6","slug":"management-of-suspected-retinal-detachment","fullItemName":"Scenario: Management of suspected retinal detachment"}]},{"id":"507ad581-89f3-5a8b-b7f6-d3c23c780501","fullItemName":"Supporting evidence","slug":"supporting-evidence","subChapters":[]},{"id":"5425d569-e730-5517-8222-3ac05f1bb17d","fullItemName":"How this topic was developed","slug":"how-this-topic-was-developed","subChapters":[{"id":"b5dddbad-7405-558b-8fa5-2520346a4078","slug":"search-strategy","fullItemName":"Search strategy"},{"id":"9bd58e75-86f4-5e47-8cd9-1e4237228e97","slug":"stakeholder-engagement","fullItemName":"Stakeholder engagement"},{"id":"5feedef8-4110-529a-bdea-a1d7f1d1a6b1","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria"},{"id":"5c697ba5-42f1-504f-9ce2-86117e43f459","slug":"organizational-behavioural-financial-barriers","fullItemName":"Organizational, behavioural and financial barriers"},{"id":"06fa76c3-febb-5a43-b5fe-b23e58638c27","slug":"declarations-of-interest","fullItemName":"Declarations of interest"}]},{"id":"3b42abd9-54a2-5f1c-8dd7-1b5475530ebd","fullItemName":"References","slug":"references","subChapters":[]}]},"parentChapter":{"id":"043a146b-8512-55b9-9f09-5d5cfe0e6149","slug":"diagnosis","fullItemName":"Diagnosis"},"subChapters":[{"id":"672264b7-8e34-5907-ac9f-11046b43782c","slug":"basis-for-recommendation-831","fullItemName":"Basis for recommendation","depth":3,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 36f04507-433d-42d1-990c-aab60116d51d --><h3>Basis for recommendation</h3><!-- end field 36f04507-433d-42d1-990c-aab60116d51d -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 83168fc3-15c8-4ba3-bd92-aab60116d4f6 --><!-- begin field ceb3230a-7900-4445-916f-aab60116d51d --><p>The recommendations on the assessment of suspected retinal detachment are largely based on the College of Optometrists clinical guidance <em>Examining patients who present with flashes and floaters</em> [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/retinal-detachment/references/\">College of Optometrists, 2019</a>], the Royal College of Ophthalmologists clinical guidance <em>Management of acute retinal detachment </em>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/retinal-detachment/references/\">Royal College of Ophthalmologists, 2010</a>], and expert opinion in review articles on retinal detachment [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/retinal-detachment/references/\">Gariano and Kim, 2004</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/retinal-detachment/references/\">Kang and Luff, 2008</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/retinal-detachment/references/\">Lumi, 2015</a>], on flashes and floaters [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/retinal-detachment/references/\">Khan, 2013</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/retinal-detachment/references/\">Sharma, 2015</a>], and on loss of vision [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/retinal-detachment/references/\">Borooah, 2015</a>].</p><ul><li>The information on the nature of flashes and floaters is based on expert opinion in review articles [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/retinal-detachment/references/\">Khan, 2013</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/retinal-detachment/references/\">Lumi, 2015</a>].</li></ul><!-- end field ceb3230a-7900-4445-916f-aab60116d51d --><!-- end item 83168fc3-15c8-4ba3-bd92-aab60116d4f6 -->","subChapters":[]}]}}},"staticQueryHashes":["3666801979"]}